1  hinge to window frame  3.5X5mm  countersunk
2  latch to window frame   4X6mm fillister (whatever that means)
3. latch to body 4X12 countersunk chrome

Now the kicker. In the PARTS BOOK there are numerous different numbers and
lengths for certain screws that do the same thing. Some are by chassis
number some say nothing. All I can figure is that some must be oval head
slotted or phillips and or also flat head slotted or phillips, some for with
panels some without, gets very confusing. This is why I asked. Not getting
anal just trying to stock all the correct screws for the correct year and
application. I have finally found an metric screw importer that has all of
the odd ball screws in all configurations. 

ronnie

